ican) 51.4% <br> [[Garrett Michael Hayes|Garrett Hayes]] (Libertarian) 2.3%\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFB3B3\" \n|'''[[Hawaii gubernatorial election, 2002|Hawaii]]'''\n| bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | [[Ben Cayetano]]\n|[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n|Term-limited, Republican victory\n|'''[[Linda Lingle]]''' (Republican) 51.6% <br> [[Mazie Hirono]] (Democratic) 47%<br> [[Kau`i Hill]] (Natural Law) 0.7%<br> [[Tracy Ryan (politician)|Tracy Ryan]] (Libertarian) 0.4%<br> [[Jim Brewer (politician)|Jim Brewer]] (Independent) 0.3%\n|-\n|'''[[2002 Idaho gubernatorial election|Idaho]]'''\n|'''[[Dirk Kempthorne]]'''\n|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|Re-elected, 56.3%\n|[[Jerry Brady]] (Democratic) 41.7% <br> [[Daniel Adams (politician)|Daniel Adams]] (Libertarian) 2%\n|- bgcolor=\"lightblue\" \n|'''[[2002 Illinois gubernatorial election|Illinois]]'''\n| bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | [[George Ryan]]\n|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|Retired, Democratic victory\n|'''[[Rod Blagojevich]]''' (Democratic) 52.2% <br> [[Jim Ryan (politician)|Jim Ryan]] (Republican) 45.1% <br> [[Cal Skinner]] (Libertarian) 2.1%\n|-\n|'''[[2002 Iowa gubernatorial election|Iowa]]'''\n|'''[[Tom Vilsack]]'''\n|[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n|Re-elected, 52.7%\n|[[Doug Gross]] (Republican) 44.5% <br> [[Jay Robinson (politician)|Jay Robinson]] (Green) 1.4% <br> [[Clyde Cleveland]] (Libertarian) 1.3%\n|- bgcolor=\"lightblue\" \n|'''[[2002 Kansas gubernatorial election|Kansas]]'''\n| bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | [[Bill Graves]]\n|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|Term-limited, Democratic victory\n|'''[[Kathleen Sebelius]]''' (Democratic) 52.9% <br> [[Tim Shallenburger]] (Republican) 45.1%<br> [[Ted Pettibone]] (Reform) 1.1%<br> [[Dennis Hawver]] (Libertarian) 1.0% \n|- bgcolor=\"lightblue\" \n|'''[[2002 Maine gubernatorial election|Maine]]'''\n| bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | [[Angus King]]\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n|Term-limited, Democratic 