 L. Williams|Lloyd Williams]] (Independent) 1.48%<br>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[2002 United States elections]]\n**[[2002 United States Senate elections]]\n**[[2002 United States House of Representatives elections]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://edition.cnn.com/ELECTION/2002/pages/governor/index.html Election 2002 \u2013 Governor]. CNN.\n\n{{United States general elections, 2002}}\n{{USGovElections}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:United States Gubernatorial Elections, 2002}}\n[[Category:2002 elections in the United States|Gubernatorial]]\n[[Category:Gubernatorial elections in the United States by year|2002]]\n[[Category:2002 United States gubernatorial elections| ]]\n[[Category:November 2002 events in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Tassedethe", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - Repaired 1 link to disambiguation page -(You can help)-Gary Richardson", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2002_United_States_gubernatorial_elections"}
{"title_page": "2020 Major League Baseball draft", "text_new": "{{Infobox sports draft\n| name        = 2020 Major League Baseball draft\n| image       = \n| date        = July 2020\n| location    = [[Omaha, Nebraska]]\n| network     = [[Fox Major League Baseball|Fox]]/[[MLB Network]]\n| league      =\n| first       = TBD<br>[[Detroit Tigers]]\n| most        = \n| fewest      =  \n| first_round = 37\n| overall     = TBD\n| rounds      = 5\n| prev        = [[2019 Major League Baseball draft|2019]]\n| next        = \n}}\nThe '''2020 Major League Baseball First-Year Player Draft''' will take place in July 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/28960271/sources-mlb-mlbpa-agree-deal-stoppage|title=Sources: MLB, MLBPA agree to deal on stoppage|date=March 27, 2020|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref> The draft will assign amateur baseball players to [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB) teams. The draft order will be set based on the reverse order of the [[2019 Major League Baseball season|2019 MLB season]] standings. In addition, compensation picks will be distributed for players who did not sign from the [[2019 Major League Baseball draft|2019 MLB Draft]] and for teams who lose qualifying [[free agent]]s.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jon|last=Tayler|url=https://www.si.com/mlb/2017/11/07/mlb-free-agency-compensation-rules-draft-picks-qualifying-offer|title=MLB's New Free Agent Compensation Rules Are Incredibly Complicated, So Let's Break Them Down|work=Sports Illustrated|date=November 7, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref> On March 26, 2020, MLB and the [[MLBPA]] reached a deal that includes the option to shorten the draft to five rounds, and also shorten the 2021 draft to 20 rounds.<ref>{{cite web|first=Bill|last=Baer|url=https://mlb.nbcsports.com/2020/03/26/mlb-mlbpa-reach-agreement-on-service-time-pay-draft/|title=MLB, MLBPA reach agreement on service time, pay, draft|work=NBC Sports|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nWith the worst record in the [[2019 MLB season]], the [[Detroit Tigers]] will receive the first overall pick.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jason|last=Beck|title=Tigers lock up top pick in 2020 MLB Draft|url=https://www.mlb.com/tigers/news/tigers-will-get-top-pick-in-2020-mlb-draft|website=MLB.com|date=September 25, 2019|accessdate=September 26, 2019}}</ref> As punishment for their role in the [[Houston Astros sign stealing scandal|sign stealing scandal]], the [[Houston Astros]] will forfeit their first- and second-round picks in the draft.<ref>{{cite web|first=Bradford William|last=Davis|title=Manager A.J. Hinch, GM Jeff Luhnow get one-year suspensions for Astros\u2019 sign-stealing; Carlos Beltran not punished|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/sports/baseball/ny-astros-sign-stealing-20200113-34pswr4hjncxdkllysi5w2iud4-story.html|website=New York Daily News|date=January 13, 2020|accessdate=January 13, 2020}}</ref> The [[Boston Red Sox]] also forfeited their second round pick in the draft as punishment for their own sign-stealing violations.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/red-sox-sign-stealing-decision |title=Commissioner decision on Red Sox investigation |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=April 22, 2020 |accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Top prospects==\n:Source: MLB.com 2020 Prospect Watch.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Prospect Watch: 100 Draft |url=http://m.mlb.com/prospects/2020?list=draft |publisher=MLB Prospect Watch |accessdate=December 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width=74%\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Ranking\n! scope=\"col\"| Player\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n! scope=\"col\"| School\n|-\n|1\n|[[Emerson Hancock]]\n|[[Pitcher]]\n|[[Georgia Bulldogs baseball|Georgia]]\n|-\n|2\n|[[Spencer Torkelson]]\n|[[First baseman]]\n|[[Arizona State Sun Devils baseball|Arizona State]]\n|-\n|3\n|[[Austin Martin]]\n|[[Shortstop]]\n|[[Vanderbilt Commodores baseball|Vanderbilt]]\n|-\n|4\n|[[Nick Gonzales]]