ptember 25, 2019|accessdate=September 26, 2019}}</ref> As punishment for their role in the [[Houston Astros sign stealing scandal|sign stealing scandal]], the [[Houston Astros]] will forfeit their first- and second-round picks in the draft.<ref>{{cite web|first=Bradford William|last=Davis|title=Manager A.J. Hinch, GM Jeff Luhnow get one-year suspensions for Astros\u2019 sign-stealing; Carlos Beltran not punished|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/sports/baseball/ny-astros-sign-stealing-20200113-34pswr4hjncxdkllysi5w2iud4-story.html|website=New York Daily News|date=January 13, 2020|accessdate=January 13, 2020}}</ref> The [[Boston Red Sox]] also forfeited their second round pick in the draft as punishment for their own sign-stealing violations.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/red-sox-sign-stealing-decision |title=Commissioner decision on Red Sox investigation |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=April 22, 2020 |accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Top prospects==\n:Source: MLB.com 2020 Prospect Watch.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Prospect Watch: 100 Draft |url=http://m.mlb.com/prospects/2020?list=draft |publisher=MLB Prospect Watch |accessdate=December 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width=74%\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Ranking\n! scope=\"col\"| Player\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n! scope=\"col\"| School\n|-\n|1\n|[[Emerson Hancock]]\n|[[Pitcher]]\n|[[Georgia Bulldogs baseball|Georgia]]\n|-\n|2\n|[[Spencer Torkelson]]\n|[[First baseman]]\n|[[Arizona State Sun Devils baseball|Arizona State]]\n|-\n|3\n|[[Austin Martin]]\n|[[Shortstop]]\n|[[Vanderbilt Commodores baseball|Vanderbilt]]\n|-\n|4\n|[[Nick Gonzales]]\n|[[Second baseman]]\n|[[New Mexico State Aggies baseball|New Mexico State]]\n|-\n|5\n|[[Asa Lacy]]\n|[[Pitcher]]\n|[[Texas A&M Aggies baseball|Texas A&M]]\n|-\n|6\n|[[Garrett Mitchell (baseball)|Garrett Mitchell]]\n|[[Outfielder]]\n|[[UCLA Bruins baseball|UCLA]]\n|-\n|7\n|[[Jared Kelley]]\n|[[Pitcher]]\n|